definitions.definition: Cut in the edge into points or inequalities , like teeth ; dented on the surface ; jagged ; notched ; stamped in.
Having an irregular , uneven ; sinuous ; undulating .
Notched like the part of a saw consisting of the teeth; serrated . A chevron indented.
Bound out by an indenture ; apprenticed ; indentured .
Notched along the margin with a different colour , like the feathers of some birds .
